<div class="section" style="margin-top:12px;">
  <div class="section-header"><span class="section-num">16</span><span class="section-title">User Feedback Themes</span></div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <p class="para"><strong>User: Customer (online and in-store)</strong></p>
    <div class="positive-label">Top Positive Themes</div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">1.</span>Product quality and range</div><div class="theme-text">Customers consistently praise product quality, range breadth, and value relative to price. Particularly strong for own-brand clothing and homeware. "Great service and good quality products at reasonable prices." (Source: Trustpilot — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">2.</span>Delivery speed and reliability</div><div class="theme-text">Next-day delivery and Click &amp; Collect consistently praised. "Delivery is quick and returns are easy." Many reviewers cite delivery speed as a primary loyalty driver. (Source: Trustpilot — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">3.</span>In-store returns experience</div><div class="theme-text">Free and easy in-store returns frequently highlighted as a core convenience benefit. "Prompt delivery service with no problem regarding unwanted items which can be returned and refunded in store." (Source: Trustpilot — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">4.</span>Staff helpfulness</div><div class="theme-text">In-store staff praised for helpfulness and friendliness. Click &amp; Collect interactions specifically commended. Indicates existing positive associate-customer relationship as a platform for loyalty recognition enhancement. (Source: Trustpilot — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">5.</span>App usability (pre-replatform)</div><div class="theme-text">While the app has known bugs, many reviewers describe it as easy to navigate and a primary shopping channel. "The app is easy to navigate and order from." (Source: Trustpilot — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="negative-label">Top Negative Themes</div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">1.</span>Delivery failures and courier reliability</div><div class="theme-text">The most common negative theme — items lost in transit, incorrect deliveries, and unreliable Evri delivery experiences. "Delivery non-existent. Waited a week to be told items lost in transit." (Source: Trustpilot — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">2.</span>Returns friction — identity fragmentation</div><div class="theme-text">Multiple reviews describe failed returns due to account identity issues — orders not found on system, mismatch between online and store records. "Coat returned with no record of online purchase on their system — spent 20 mins while they went through the till looking for my order." (Source: Trustpilot — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">3.</span>Customer service slow response</div><div class="theme-text">Email response delays and unresolved refund issues are frequently cited. A reviewer waited several weeks for a £24 refund, eventually discovering Next had "accidentally deleted" their account. (Source: Sitejabber — next.co.uk)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">4.</span>App bugs and inconsistency</div><div class="theme-text">Favourites, basket, and wish list instability noted by multiple reviewers. Next acknowledged "ongoing issues" with the favourites feature in March 2024 and has committed to the native app replatform for 2025. (Source: Google Play — Next app)</div></div>
    <div class="theme-item"><div class="theme-title"><span class="theme-num">5.</span>Absence of loyalty recognition for long-tenure customers</div><div class="theme-text">Not surfaced as a specific review theme but confirmed structurally — the external confirmation that Next has "no conventional loyalty scheme" is widely noted by discount tracking sites, signalling an unmet expectation gap in the market. (Source: dontpayfull.com)</div></div>
